             sworn.</p>
               <p>I live in Gracechurch-street. I know Mr. Spode; he lives in Fore-street. On the <rs id="t17900915-118-cd613" type="crimeDate">24th of July</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900915-118-off612 t17900915-118-cd613"></join> the prisoner came to my house, about eleven o'clock, and tendered me this note; I asked who he came from in Fore-street? he said, from Mr. Spode: I told him I had no full half pint tumblers; but I had small ones; he said, it was small ones were wanted, and that he was going to Leadenhall-street, and would call again presently; he came back again; I had them nearly ready; I made out a bill of parcels, and delivered them to him, and he went away: I never saw him before to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>(The note read.)</p>
               <p>Court. Are you sure as to his person? - Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17900915-118-person1157">
                  WILLIAM
                   COPELAND
